{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T17:57:49.178Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Entropy"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"KL Divergence"},{"type":"text","text":" are fundamental concepts in information theory that quantify uncertainty and measure distances between probability distributions—entropy measures the average \"surprise\" or uncertainty in a random variable's outcomes, while KL Divergence measures how much information is lost when one distribution approximates another, making them essential for training generative models, cross-entropy loss, and understanding model uncertainty in machine learning."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Entropy (Shannon Entropy):"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Definition"},{"type":"text","text":": Entropy quantifies the average level of "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"uncertainty or surprise"},{"type":"text","text":" present in a random variable's possible outcomes."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mathematical formula"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"H(X) = - Σ P(x) × log_b P(x)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"H(X)"},{"type":"text","text":" = entropy of random variable X\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"P(x)"},{"type":"text","text":" = probability of outcome x\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"b"},{"type":"text","text":" = base of logarithm (usually 2 for bits, e for nats)\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Negative sign"},{"type":"text","text":" = ensures positive entropy (since log of probability < 1 is negative)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Alternative form"},{"type":"text","text":" (expected value):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"H(X) = E[I(x)] = -Σ p_i log₂(p_i)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where I(x) = information content (surprisal) of outcome x."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Intuitive meaning:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Entropy = average \"surprise\" when you observe an outcome\n\nHigh entropy: Outcomes are unpredictable (uniform distribution)\n- Example: Fair coin (50% heads, 50% tails) → HIGH uncertainty\n\nLow entropy: Outcomes are predictable (one outcome dominates)\n- Example: Biased coin (99% heads, 1% tails) → LOW uncertainty [web:297][web:301]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key insight"},{"type":"text","text":": The more unpredictable an event is, the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"higher its entropy"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"KL Divergence (Kullback-Leibler Divergence):"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Definition"},{"type":"text","text":": KL Divergence measures the "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"difference between two probability distributions"},{"type":"text","text":" P and Q—it quantifies how much information is lost when Q approximates P."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Also called"},{"type":"text","text":": Information gain, relative entropy."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mathematical formula"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"D_KL(P||Q) = Σ P(x) × log(P(x) / Q(x))"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For continuous distributions:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"D_KL(P||Q) = ∫ P(x) × log(P(x) / Q(x)) dx"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Where:\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"P(x)"},{"type":"text","text":" = true distribution\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Q(x)"},{"type":"text","text":" = approximating/model distribution\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"log(P(x)/Q(x))"},{"type":"text","text":" = ratio of probabilities (how different they are)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Intuitive meaning:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"KL Divergence = \"extra bits\" you need when encoding data using wrong distribution\n\nImagine compressing weather data:\n- True distribution P: Actual weather probabilities\n- Approximate distribution Q: Your model's predicted probabilities\n\nD_KL(P||Q) = extra bits needed to encode reality using Q instead of P [web:300]\n\nKL Divergence is the amount of extra information required to predict the weather using your model instead of the true distribution [web:300]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Why it matters — Importance in Generative AI"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Entropy and KL Divergence are critical for:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ML Application"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"How entropy/KL apply"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cross-Entropy Loss"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Standard loss for classification; minimizes KL between true and predicted"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"VAEs"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Minimize KL divergence between latent distribution and prior (usually Gaussian)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"GANs"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Optimize to minimize KL between generated and real data distributions"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Information Theory"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Entropy quantifies information in messages/data"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Data Compression"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Entropy determines limit on encoding efficiency"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Uncertainty Quantification"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"High entropy = uncertain predictions"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Real example"},{"type":"text","text":": Training GPT-4 uses cross-entropy loss (equivalent to KL divergence) to minimize differences between predicted and actual next tokens."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key properties"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Entropy properties:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Property"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Description"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Non-negative"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"H(X) ≥ 0"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Maximum for uniform"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"H(X) is highest when all outcomes equally likely"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero for certain"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"H(X) = 0 if P(x) = 1 for one outcome (no uncertainty)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Bits vs nats"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"log₂ → bits; logₑ → nats"}]}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Examples"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fair coin (P=0.5, Q=0.5):\nH(X) = -[0.5×log₂(0.5) + 0.5×log₂(0.5)]\n     = -[0.5×(-1) + 0.5×(-1)]\n     = 1 bit [max uncertainty]\n\nBiased coin (P=0.99, Q=0.01):\nH(X) = -[0.99×log₂(0.99) + 0.01×log₂(0.01)]\n     ≈ -[0.99×(-0.014) + 0.01×(-6.64)]\n     ≈ 0.08 bits [low uncertainty] [web:297]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"KL Divergence properties:"}]},{"type":"table","content":[{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Property"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Description"}]}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableHeader","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Non-negative"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"D_KL(P"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Q) ≥ 0 (always)"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero if equal"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"D_KL(P"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Q) = 0 only if P = Q"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Asymmetric"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"D_KL(P"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Q) ≠ D_KL(Q"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"P)"}]}]}]},{"type":"tableRow","content":[{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Not a metric"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Doesn't satisfy triangle inequality"}]}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"tableCell","attrs":{"colspan":1,"rowspan":1,"colwidth":null,"align":null},"content":[{"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key insight"},{"type":"text","text":": KL divergence is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"always non-negative"},{"type":"text","text":" because it quantifies information loss when approximating P with Q—you can never have \"negative information loss\"."}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"How to compute — Step-by-step examples"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 1: Entropy of fair coin"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Outcomes: Heads (P=0.5), Tails (P=0.5)\n\nH(X) = - Σ P(x) × log₂ P(x)\n     = -[0.5 × log₂(0.5) + 0.5 × log₂(0.5)]\n     = -[0.5 × (-1) + 0.5 × (-1)]\n     = -[-0.5 - 0.5]\n     = 1 bit\n\nInterpretation: 1 bit of uncertainty (max for coin)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 2: Entropy of biased coin"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Outcomes: Heads (P=0.9), Tails (P=0.1)\n\nH(X) = -[0.9 × log₂(0.9) + 0.1 × log₂(0.1)]\n     = -[0.9 × (-0.152) + 0.1 × (-3.322)]\n     = -[-0.137 - 0.332]\n     = 0.469 bits\n\nInterpretation: 0.469 bits of uncertainty (low, since biased)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Example 3: KL Divergence between two distributions"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"True distribution P: [0.5, 0.3, 0.2]\nApproximate Q: [0.4, 0.4, 0.2]\n\nD_KL(P||Q) = Σ P(x) × log(P(x) / Q(x))\n           = 0.5 × log(0.5/0.4) + 0.3 × log(0.3/0.4) + 0.2 × log(0.2/0.2)\n           = 0.5 × log(1.25) + 0.3 × log(0.75) + 0.2 × log(1.0)\n           = 0.5 × 0.097 + 0.3 × (-0.125) + 0.2 × 0\n           = 0.049 - 0.038 + 0\n           = 0.011 nats\n\nInterpretation: Small KL → Q is close approximation of P"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Python implementation"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Computing entropy:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import numpy as np\n\n# Probability distribution\nprobs = [0.5, 0.3, 0.2]\n\n# Entropy (bits)\nentropy = -np.sum(probs * np.log2(probs))\nprint(f\"Entropy: {entropy:.3f} bits\")  # ≈ 1.489 bits"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Computing KL divergence:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import numpy as np\n\n# True distribution P\nP = np.array([0.5, 0.3, 0.2])\n\n# Approximate distribution Q\nQ = np.array([0.4, 0.4, 0.2])\n\n# KL Divergence (nats)\nkl_div = np.sum(P * np.log(P / Q))\nprint(f\"KL Divergence: {kl_div:.3f} nats\")  # ≈ 0.011 nats"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cross-entropy loss (equivalent to KL + entropy):"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"python"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"import numpy as np\n\n# True labels (one-hot)\ntrue = np.array([1, 0, 0])  # Class 0 is correct\n\n# Predicted probabilities\npred = np.array([0.7, 0.2, 0.1])\n\n# Cross-entropy loss\nloss = -np.sum(true * np.log(pred))\nprint(f\"Cross-entropy loss: {loss:.3f}\")  # ≈ 0.357\n\n# Relationship: Cross-entropy = KL(P||Q) + Entropy(P)"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"KL Divergence vs Cross-Entropy"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key relationship:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cross-Entropy(P, Q) = Entropy(P) + D_KL(P||Q)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Why this matters"},{"type":"text","text":":\n- Entropy(P) is fixed (depends only on true distribution)\n- Minimizing cross-entropy = minimizing KL divergence"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"In machine learning"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Cross-entropy loss equates to minimizing the distance between distributions [web:298]\n\nBy minimizing cross-entropy, we're minimizing the distance between distributions [web:298]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Interpretation of KL Divergence"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Asymmetric meaning:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"D_KL(P||Q) ≠ D_KL(Q||P)\n\nP||Q: Extra bits when using Q to approximate P (true → model)\nQ||P: Extra bits when using P to approximate Q (model → true)\n\nDirection matters! [web:298][web:306]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Non-negativity proof intuition:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"KL = Σ P(x) × log(P(x)/Q(x))\n\nUsing log(x) ≥ 1 - 1/x (for x > 0):\nlog(P/Q) ≥ 1 - Q/P\n\nMultiply by P:\nP × log(P/Q) ≥ P - Q\n\nSum over all x:\nΣ P × log(P/Q) ≥ Σ(P - Q) = 0\n\nThus KL ≥ 0 [web:302]"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Key takeaways"}]},{"type":"orderedList","attrs":{"start":1,"type":null},"content":[{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Entropy = average uncertainty"},{"type":"text","text":": H(X) = -Σ P(x) log P(x)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"High entropy"},{"type":"text","text":": Unpredictable outcomes (uniform distribution)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Low entropy"},{"type":"text","text":": Predictable outcomes (one outcome dominates)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Entropy max"},{"type":"text","text":": Uniform distribution (all outcomes equally likely)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Entropy zero"},{"type":"text","text":": Certain outcome (P=1 for one outcome)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Bits vs nats"},{"type":"text","text":": log₂ → bits; logₑ → nats"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"KL Divergence"},{"type":"text","text":": Distance between distributions: D_KL(P||Q) = Σ P log(P/Q)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"KL meaning"},{"type":"text","text":": Extra bits needed when using Q instead of P for encoding"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Non-negative"},{"type":"text","text":": D_KL ≥ 0 (always)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Zero if equal"},{"type":"text","text":": D_KL = 0 only when P = Q"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Asymmetric"},{"type":"text","text":": D_KL(P||Q) ≠ D_KL(Q||P)"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Cross-entropy = KL + entropy"},{"type":"text","text":": Minimizing cross-entropy = minimizing KL"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"VAEs"},{"type":"text","text":": Minimize KL between latent distribution and prior"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Classification"},{"type":"text","text":": Cross-entropy loss minimizes KL between true and predicted"}]}]},{"type":"listItem","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Data compression"},{"type":"text","text":": Entropy determines limit on encoding efficiency"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"For Generative AI, entropy and KL Divergence are fundamental: VAEs use KL to regularize latent spaces, GANs optimize to minimize KL between generated and real distributions, cross-entropy loss (equivalent to KL) trains classifiers, and entropy quantifies uncertainty in model predictions—making them essential for understanding how generative models learn and generate data."}]}]}}
